Here's what happened.<br /><br />The download mirror service called FossHub, where Classic Shell stores its downloads, got hacked earlier today. This was intended to coincide with the release of Windows 10 Anniversary Update, which would cause many people to have to download the latest Classic Shell.<br /><br />The installer got replaced with a malicious software that corrupts your MBR (which is where the PC stores its drive information).<br /><br />As soon as the hack was reported, I replaced the download links with clean ones. The FossHub page is down, pending investigation.<br /><br />I understand if you are reluctant to trust Classic Shell again, however a simple test can show you if the download is legitimate - look at the file properties and check for digital certificate. The fake file doesn't have a certificate.<br /><br />Check out this forum post for possible remedy: <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=12&amp;t=6434#p27967">viewtopic.php?f=12&amp;t=6434#p27967</a><!-- l --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Tue Aug 02, 2016 7:06 pm</p><hr />
